Bavaria's state premier, Markus Söder, on Wednesday offered the newest member of the British royal family, whose name was announced Wednesday as Archie Harrison Mountbatten-Windsor, a very Bavarian present: a tiny pair of Lederhosen. Prince Harry, Meghan and Baby Sussex "A real pair of Lederhosen, so that the Bavarian way of life may accompany the little one from the beginning," Söder wrote on Twitter as he congratulated Prince Charles and his wife Camilla on becoming grandparents. Söder will be welcoming the royal couple to Bavaria on Thursday. Prince Harry and his wife Meghan, the Duchess of Sussex, welcomed their first child into the world early Monday, while Charles and Camilla have been on a tour of Germany. Regal presents On Tuesday Prince Charles and Camilla met Chancellor Angela Merkel and were presented with a teddy bear for their newborn grandson by President Frank-Walter Steinmeier. Smiles all around as Steinmeier surprises Prince Charles with a gift for his grandson Prince Harry and Meghan have received an outpouring of support from around the world since the birth was announced. In a post on Instagram, the royal couple asked people not to send gifts, but to donate to their chosen charities instead. av/jm (dpa, pnp) Each evening at 1830 UTC, DW's editors send out a selection of the day's hard news and quality feature journalism. You can sign up to receive it directly here. 